{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XYC7icoCRqW2gyD33ayddi","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me now create a comprehensive summary of all the routing information I've found:\n\n## Summary: URL Routing and Endpoint Definitions\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase for all URL routing, handler definitions, and gRPC service definitions related to runs and projects endpoints. Here are the findings:\n\n### HTTP Router Configuration\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe application uses Go's built-in `http.ServeMux` (initialized at line 128). All routes are registered in the `NewHandler` function (lines 139-158):\n\n#### HTML Page Routes\n- `GET /{$}` → `handleProjectOverview` (landing page showing all projects)\n- `GET /runs` → `handleRunsList` \n- `GET /runs/{id}` → `handleRunDetail`\n- `GET /projects/{name}` → `handleProjectDetail`\n\n#### JSON API Routes for Runs\n- `GET /api/runs` → `handleAPIRuns` (list all runs or filter by project)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` → `handleAPIRunDetail` (get single run with step details)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` → `handleAPIStepOutput` (fetch step logs)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` → `handleAPIStream` (SSE streaming of live logs)\n- `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` → `handleAPIDeleteContainer`\n\n#### JSON API Routes for Projects\n- `GET /api/projects` → `handleAPIProjects`\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}` → (resolved via `resolveProjectDir`)\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info` → `handleAPIProjectInfo`\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` → `handleAPIPromptDiff`\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows` → `handleAPIWorkflows`\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` → `handleAPIStepContent`\n\n#### Orchestrator Control Routes\n- `GET /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStatus`\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStart`\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop` → `handleAPIOrchestratorStop`\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency` → `handleAPIOrchestratorConcurrency`\n- `POST /api/projects/{name}/trigger` → `handleAPITriggerOrchestrator`\n\n#### Static Files\n- `GET /static/*` → served via `http.FileServerFS`\n\n### Query Parameter Filtering\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe following endpoints support query parameter based filtering:\n\n1. **For `/runs` (HTML)** (line 249):\n   - Query param: `?project=<directory_path>`\n   - Handler checks: `projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")`\n   - If set, calls `h.store.ListRunsByProject()`, else calls `h.store.ListRuns()`\n\n2. **For `/api/runs` (JSON API)** (line 448):\n   - Query param: `?project=<directory_path>`\n   - Handler checks: `projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")`\n   - Same logic: filters runs by project directory\n\n3. **For `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`** (line 566):\n   - Query param: `?type=<\"script\"|\"llm\">`\n   - Optional type filter for log files\n\n4. **For `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff`** (lines 1032-1033):\n   - Query params: `?file=<path>&sha=<commit_sha>`\n   - Used to show git diff for prompt files\n\n**Test Examples:**\n- `/runs?project=/home/user/alpha` (line 286 in handler_test.go)\n- `/api/runs?project=/home/user/alpha` (line 325 in handler_test.go)\n\n### gRPC Service Definition\n\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\nThe gRPC service `ClocheService` has 8 RPCs (none have project-based filtering built in):\n\n1. `rpc RunWorkflow(RunWorkflowRequest) returns (RunWorkflowResponse)`\n   - Payload includes: workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt, keep_container\n\n2. `rpc GetStatus(GetStatusRequest) returns (GetStatusResponse)`\n   - Request: run_id\n   - Response includes: state, steps, container_id\n\n3. `rpc StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry)`\n   - Request params: run_id, step_name (optional), log_type (optional)\n   - Line 468 in server.go handles filtering by step_name/log_type\n\n4. `rpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) returns (StopRunResponse)`\n   - Request: run_id\n\n5. `rpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse)`\n   - Request: all (bool) — if false, returns last 1 hour of runs\n   - Line 382-404 in server.go: no project filtering at gRPC level\n\n6. `rpc Orchestrate(OrchestrateRequest) returns (OrchestrateResponse)`\n   - Request: project_dir\n   - Response: dispatched (count)\n\n7. `rpc Shutdown(ShutdownRequest) returns (ShutdownResponse)`\n\n8. `rpc DeleteContainer(DeleteContainerRequest) returns (DeleteContainerResponse)`\n   - Request: id (can be run_id or container_id)\n\n### gRPC Implementation\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\nKey implementation details:\n- `ListRuns` (line 382): Filters by time only (1 hour default), no project field in request\n- `StreamLogs` (line 458): Supports filtering by step_name and log_type via request fields\n- `Orchestrate` (line 685): Takes project_dir in request\n\n### Key Observations\n\n1. **HTTP has query-param filtering** for runs by project (`?project=<dir>`), but gRPC's `ListRuns` doesn't expose this\n2. **Project resolution** happens via label matching (handler_test.go line 249-266 shows label generation from directory paths)\n3. **No dedicated \"GetProjectRuns\" endpoint** — filtering is done in handlers by calling `ListRunsByProject()` store method\n4. **gRPC filtering is step/type based** (for logs) but not project-based at the RPC level\n5. Path parameters use Go 1.22+ pattern syntax (`{id}`, `{name}`) with optional `{$}` for exact matching\n\n---\n\n**Absolute file paths:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (HTTP routes and query handling)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (gRPC service implementation)\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (gRPC service definition)\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (daemon setup)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` (test cases with examples)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3875ddf8813f799d (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61117\ntool_uses: 15\nduration_ms: 29967</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5417fe53-38fc-4081-a53f-ab0580b28d18","uuid":"fea5b032-7665-4444-9f6c-daa995823151","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find all files related to URL routing, particularly for \"runs\" and \"projects\" endpoints. Search for:\n1. HTTP route/handler definitions (look for patterns like mux, router, HandleFunc, Handle, http.NewServeMux, chi, gin, gorilla, etc.)\n2. Any references to \"runs?project=\" or query parameter based project filtering for runs\n3. Any gRPC service definitions related to runs and projects\n4. Files in cmd/ and internal/adapters/ that define API endpoints\n\nBe very thorough - check all Go files for route patterns, URL construction, and handler registration.","agentId":"a3875ddf8813f799d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Let me now create a comprehensive summary of all the routing information I've found:\n\n## Summary: URL Routing and Endpoint Definitions\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase for all URL routing, handler definitions, and gRPC service definitions related to runs and projects endpoints. Here are the findings:\n\n### HTTP Router Configuration\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe application uses Go's built-in `http.ServeMux` (initialized at line 128). All routes are registered in the `NewHandler` function (lines 139-158):\n\n#### HTML Page Routes\n- `GET /{$}` → `handleProjectOverview` (landing page showing all projects)\n- `GET /runs` → `handleRunsList` \n- `GET /runs/{id}` → `handleRunDetail`\n- `GET /projects/{name}` → `handleProjectDetail`\n\n#### JSON API Routes for Runs\n- `GET /api/runs` → `handleAPIRuns` (list all runs or filter 